# Visualizing DagsHub Datasets with RepoViz 

## Introduction

In the ever-evolving landscape of machine learning, visualizing and understanding your data quickly and effectively is paramount. That's why we are thrilled to introduce our new application designed to seamlessly integrate with DagsHub repositories, offering powerful data visualization capabilities to elevate your projects.

## Background on DagsHub

DagsHub is a collaborative platform for data scientists and machine learning practitioners. It provides a comprehensive suite of tools for versioning, sharing, and collaborating on data and machine learning projects. While DagsHub excels in managing data and workflows, we saw an opportunity to enhance its visualization capabilities for exploratory data analysis.

## Introducing RepoViz

## How It Works

Our application leverages the DagsHub API to access data directly from your repositories. Once your repository is specified, you can select the datasets you with to visualize 

![][image3]

Once the dataset is loaded, you are given the option to visualize the data using three exploratory data analysis tools: D-Tale, SweetViz, and YData.

![][image4]

## D-Tale

D-Tale is an interactive data exploration tool for analyzing Pandas dataframes. On the main page of its web UI you can interact directly with the loaded dataset using filtering, sorting, and conditional formatting.

![][image5]

D-Tale supports exploratory data analysis through automatically generated tables and statistical summaries. In addition, you can create and customize various visualizations, including histograms, scatter plots, and heatmaps via its chart interface.

![][image6]

## SweetViz

SweetViz creates a comprehensive report that includes essential statistics, missing value analysis, and visualizations for distributions and correlations.

![][image7]

SweetViz excels in comparing two datasets, highlighting differences and similarities through intuitive and clear visuals. Below we see an example of a medical imaging dataset divided into two cohorts according to scanner type, and a target variable indicating a specific disease phenotype.

![][image8]

## YData

YData generates a report that covers distributions, correlations, missing values, and descriptive statistics. It is particularly useful for detecting data quality issues, such as outliers or inconsistencies, and for getting a holistic view of your dataset before diving into more complex analysis. 

![][image9]

YData also offers more detailed information and unique visualizations for text variables.  

![][image10]

## Future Additions

In future updates to RepoViz, we plan to introduce additional customization options for report generation, allowing users to tailor their exploratory data analysis more precisely to their needs. This will include the ability to select specific target variables and data subsets for SweetViz reports, enabling more focused and relevant insights. Additionally, we are working on integrating visualizations for annotation metadata. 

## Conclusion

By integrating powerful exploratory data analysis tools, RepoViz provides a convenient solution for uncovering insights from your DagsHub datasets. We invite you to try out RepoViz and provide feedback for how we can make this tool more impactful for your personal needs\!
